Last reminder to register for the BYU + Silicon Slopes: Growth Venture Connect Meet & Greet

*Registration will close at 4pm today.  If you register your resume will be sent out in the resume book to the company.  You can still come to the event if you do not register; however, your resume will not be included in the resume book.*

This event is a networking event NOT a hiring event but this is an opportunity to get your name on the radar of local growth stage companies.  We will have another event in the winter semester that will be focussed on hiring.

Attire: Business casual and please wear your MBA name tag

text:
Making another plug for this... if you came back from your internship and thought "I wish I had a more meaningful opportunity to go after" this is for you:

We're having an info session on *buying a business* on October 17th, 5p -6p, room TBD.
• What the economics of buying a business look like
• What the benefits to buying a business are
• How to start looking for a business to buy
• Listen to experiences from a few BYU MBA grads that have bought businesses
• Intro to the Acquisition Case Competition that will take place in November ($1000 cash prize to the winner) -- 1st/2nd years can enter
^^The Acquisition Case Comp will be on  :rotating_light: *Saturday, November 18th* :rotating_light: at the new Kiln in Provo. It will be an awesome chance to pitch your acquisition idea(s) to potential investors.

It's open to anybody, 1st or 2nd years -- just give us a thumbs up so we have a headcount for food.

This Friday around 7pm (after the temple) Kirsi and I are hiking the Y at sunset/dusk and would love to have anyone join us! :blush:
The view of the city at night is really awesome and last time I hiked the Y at night, I saw a spider the size of a baseball with green eyes shine in my headlamp and that seems really Friday the 13th vibes :eyes: :spider: :flushed:!
Equipment needed: headlamp or flashlight ( I have extras if needed!)
Friends and fam welcome too. Post :hiking_boot: below if interested!!

text:
Hey Everyone! We have a great MBA networking event coming up! Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. There will be all sorts of great companies represented there! Including but not limited to McKinsey, Bain, PWC, Slalom, Cicero, Bill, and many more! We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
Free for SCA members and $3 for non-members
Business Casual
